Template: arrowhead-common/install_type
Type: select
Choices: Detached, Authorized
Description: Do you want to perform (1) a detached, standalone install or (2) authorized install with externally issued cloud cert?

Template: arrowhead-common/cloud_cert
Type: string
Default:
Description: Enter the path for the externally issued cloud cert

Template: arrowhead-common/master_cert
Type: string
Default:
Description: Enter the path for the externally issued cloud cert

Template: arrowhead-common/cloud_password
Type: password
Default:
Description: Enter the password for the externally issued cloud cert

Template: arrowhead-common/cloud_alias
Type: string
Default:
Description: Enter the alias for the externally issued cloud cert

Template: arrowhead-common/cloudname
Type: string
Default: testcloud
Description: The name of the Arrowhead local cloud

Template: arrowhead-common/operator
Type: string
Default: user
Description: The name of the operator of the local cloud

Template: arrowhead-common/company
Type: string
Default: arrowhead
Description: The name of your company

Template: arrowhead-common/country
Type: string
Default: eu
Description: The name of your country

Template: arrowhead-common/mysql_password
Type: password
Default:
Description: Password for the MySQL database (leave empty for random). Note that password is stored by debconf in '/var/cache/debconf/passwords.dat'.

Template: arrowhead-common/cert_password
Type: password
Default:
Description: Password for the certificates and stores (leave empty for random). Note that password is stored by debconf in '/var/cache/debconf/passwords.dat'.

Template: arrowhead-common/reconf_warning
Type: note
Description: You have to manually reconfigure all Arrowhead systems when changing passwords
